<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF110-343-292  </DOCNO><DOCID>10 343 292.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DBMS  Dec 1990 v3 n13 p18(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Paradox SQL access: SQL Link provides access to SQL databaseservers via the Paradox engine. (Nested Selects) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Finkelstein, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Borland International's products have become a well-integratedsuite of application development and end-user tools.andP;  The companybegan this process by separating the Paradox Engine from theParadox development programs and creating a stand-alone data basemanagement product.andP;  The advantages of this strategy becameobvious when Borland release Pascal and C hooks into the Paradoxengine.andP;  Users can use Paradox's query by example (QBE) program orusing the Quattro spreadsheet to directly access Paradox databasesvia the Engine interface.andP;  The Paradox architecture fosters datasharing, but the engine lacks the intelligence, reliability andperformance of a centralized server.andP;  Transaction management islacking as is centralized locking, automatic database recovery andcentralized performance optimization.andP;  The vendors provided ausable way to migrate current Paradox applications to aclient/server environment.andP;  Users can choose from several databaseservers.andP;  SQL Link will, in the future, connect to DEC's Rdb/VMS,running on VAX systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Borland International Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Paradox Engine (Program development software) (Design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     Program Development ToolsC Programming LanguagePASCALStructured Query LanguageSoftware Migration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>